<br />
<br />Also I originally drafted a variant of the Social Mutiny Logo when i was in the fifth grade, btw. I used it as the brand logo for my homebrew underground comics i drew and printed on a xerox machine in order to sell for 25cents to 75cents a pop.
<br />
<br />25cents was for coloring and activity books.
<br />50cents was for 12 page comic books.
<br />75cents was for 20 page comic books.
<br />
<br />When Metroid Prime came out I obviously had to redo the logo, note the striking similarity to the Samus 'S'. when you make the bolt and 'm' portions hollow space, and make the outer edge a complete circle minus endpoints of the hollow lightning bolt.
<br />
<br />That was the logo for my original company, Zac Comics Interplanetary, when i was in grade school.

		

